<dl id="n41198e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n41" href="#n41198e">N41 (VI.B.33)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n41all.htm#n41198e"> 198(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> LC &amp; I.B newspaper / door signal</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">To begin with, we used to get up very early indeed. Our bedroom doors faced each other at the top of the staircase. When I came out of mine I always knew if I might go into his room or not by his signal. If, when I came into the passage, I found that <mark>a newspaper had been put under the door, then I knew</mark> I might go in at once; but if there was no newspaper, then I had to wait till it appeared. <small> Miss Isa Bowman, <a name="IBSL" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#IBSL"><cite title="source">The Story Of Lewis Carroll</cite></a>. (1899) 68</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
